{"author":{"id":"b815c53718a0d7121846b81e1c820fdbcf27ef19124fbf0a3f1f9fcc65f67df7"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1520361081,"nonce":"rNE+Papbjo/iCUPyqYI+lojkUeI=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM3MDg4MTE4Ng==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1754#issuecomment-370881186"},"message":"I think a preference on filters and then validators are the way to go. We shouldn't let things be selected that can't be run, and we shouldn't run things that are wrong. Probably some enhancement work needed to get this really working correctly, especially in the case of grouping constructs.\n\nAs far as the dbkey is concerned, I think we should be training and requiring users to have matching keys, otherwise very strange/wrong results can happen. Likely allowing '?' to match with '?' will prevent concerns about custom datasets that a user hasn't created a custom genome for.\n\nPerhaps during file upload, we can make it much more obvious in the GUI that a user should set a dbkey on their files. Bold, blinking, and red? Maybe a popup tooltip that gives a warning? Maybe have it dismissable by a user with memory, and only have it appear when its likely needed: for example genomic regions should have a dbkey set, fastq files shouldn't.","files":null}]}